repository-code: "https://github.com/queelius/dreamlog"
url: "https://github.com/queelius/dreamlog"
abstract: >-
  DreamLog is a logic programming system that discovers generalizable
  concepts through knowledge base compression. It implements wake-sleep
  cycles inspired by DreamCoder: wake phases answer queries via SLD
  resolution with optional LLM rule generation for undefined predicates,
  and sleep phases compress the knowledge base through nine operations
  (subsumption, redundant fact pruning, generalization with exceptions,
  predicate invention, body pattern extraction, dead clause pruning,
  LLM-assisted compression, lemma caching, and recursive closure
  discovery), each accepted only when it lowers a minimum-description-length
  objective and verified against a test suite of positive and negative
  queries with atomic rollback. The accompanying paper introduces a test
  protocol that separates compression-driven generalization from LLM
  training-data recall, using fact bases over invented vocabulary paired
  with a raw-LLM baseline.
keywords:
